    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT 
Jackson, former Union Seminary student and Congregational minister, discusses pacifism, classmates who were conscientious objectors during WWII, his participation in alternative service during the war, educational experiences and the development of his beliefs, segregation and race relations, participation in protests for racial equality and peace, labor unions, and the United Auto Workers in Detroit, Michigan. 2 tapes, 135 mins., 30 pp. 
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley, 1988 
